description: Islanders who are not essential workers can leave their homes for two hours a day only, from Monday.
title: Coronavirus: Jersey faces lockdown as islanders told stay home
title_page: Coronavirus: Jersey faces lockdown as islanders told stay home - BBC News
maintext: Deputy Renouf said: "Without timely results showing us what social distancing is doing to the spread of the infection, there is a risk that the measures are not working as well as they could."
